      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 2.5",
      "body" : "One MAJOR problem with your code -- java&#39;s byte type is SIGNED, so if the top bit of any byte is set, your code will also set all the upper bits in the resulting int.  You need to mask off the upper bits of each byte before shifting and oring, eg <code>(bytes[0] &amp; 0xff) | ((bytes[1] &amp; 0xff) &lt;&lt; 8) | ...</code>"
    }, {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 76705,
        "reputation" : 8954,
        "user_id" : 219394,
        "user_type" : "registered",
        "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/be6af8c75baccb49c9f0e6158c505973?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
        "display_name" : "Kevin Brock",
        "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/219394/kevin-brock"
      },
