    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 2.5",
    "body" : "<p>try something like this:</p>\n\n<pre><code>a = buffer[3];\na = a*256 + buffer[2];\na = a*256 + buffer[1];\na = a*256 + buffer[0];\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>this is assuming that the lowest byte comes first. if the highest byte comes first you might have to swap the indices (go from 0 to 3).</p>\n\n<p>basically for each byte you want to add, you first multiply <em>a</em> by 256 (which equals a shift to the left by 8 bits) and then add the new byte.</p>\n"
  }, {
