      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "@MikhailIonkin Your comment is wrong, and this code is correct. in.read() does not return a byte. If it did, sign extension would occur when it was stored in an int variable. But in.read() returns the next byte of the stream converted to int WITHOUT sign extension. So If the next byte of the stream is 0xFF, in.read() would return 0x000000FF. The only way in.read() will return -1 is when you reach the end of the stream."
