    "question_id" : 2383265,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>If you have them already in a byte[] array, you can use:   </p>\n\n<pre><code>int result = ByteBuffer.wrap(bytes).getInt();\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>source: <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/2840190/java-convert-4-bytes-to-int\">here</a></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1741376,
      "reputation" : 4585,
      "user_id" : 1592679,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 60,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/699172feade134107db516a54a4e0548?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Jamel Toms",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1592679/jamel-toms"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 1,
    "last_activity_date" : 1375303000,
    "creation_date" : 1375303000,
    "answer_id" : 17980487,
    "question_id" : 2383265,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>You can also use BigInteger for variable length bytes. You can convert it to Long, Integer or Short, whichever suits your needs.</p>\n\n<pre><code>new BigInteger(bytes).intValue();\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>or to denote polarity:</p>\n\n<pre><code>new BigInteger(1, bytes).intValue();\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 13134070,
      "reputation" : 11,
      "user_id" : 9487722,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/3bc2d79d0be9c901061980bbdb87ccc9?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "Mounir",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/9487722/mounir"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 1,
    "last_activity_date" : 1523080341,
    "creation_date" : 1523080341,
    "answer_id" : 49704362,
    "question_id" : 2383265,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>For reading unsigned 4 bytes as integer we should use a long variable, because the sign bit is considered as part of the unsigned number.</p>\n\n<pre><code>long result = (((bytes[0] &lt;&lt; 8 &amp; bytes[1]) &lt;&lt; 8 &amp; bytes[2]) &lt;&lt; 8) &amp; bytes[3]; \nresult = result &amp; 0xFFFFFFFF;\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>This is tested well worked function</p>\n"
  }, {
    "comments" : [ {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 1316033,
        "reputation" : 8088,
        "user_id" : 1262865,
        "user_type" : "registered",
        "accept_rate" : 50,
        "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/ojvZh.jpg?s=256",
